VIDEO: 42

BREAK FUNCTION

If a vending machine has only 4 packets and user ask for >= < 4packets
available=4
x=int(input("How many packets do you want?"))
i=1
while i<=x:
    if i>available:
        print("we are out of stock")
        break
    i=i+1
    print ("packet")
print("Thanks for your purchase \n Please visit again”)


VIDEO: 43

CONTINUE FUNCTION

Use of OR and AND function
for x in range (1,30):
    if x %6==0 and x%4==0:
        continue
    print(x)
print("Here we used AND function lets try OR function")


for x in range (1,30):
    if x %6==0 or x%4==0:
        continue
    print(x)
print("hope you understand between OR and AND function \n both divisible by 4 and 6 are ommitted")



VIDEO: 44

PASS FUNCTION

Difference between continue and pass function
for x in range (1,10):
    if x %3==0:
        print("skip")
        
        continue
    print(x)
print("Here all the divisible of 3 are replaced by SKIP/n now change CONTINUE with PASS")

print(". space \n. space\n. space\n. space\n. space\n. space")



for x in range (1,10):
    if x %3==0:
        print("skip")
        
        pass
    print(x)
print("Here here multiple of 3 remains with word SKIP")





